Frobenius Norm.
[It is called [Frobenius norm] or [Hilbert-Schmidt norm] (the latter is usually used exclusively for operators in Hilbert spaces). This [norm] has several different definitions, though,

[$ \|A\|_{F}= \sqrt{\sum_{i=1}^{m}\sum_{j=1}^{n}|a_{ij}|^{2}} = \sqrt{\mathrm{tr} (A^{*}A)} = \sqrt {\sum _{i=1}^{\min\{m,n\}} \sigma_{i}^{2}} ]
can be written as follows. where A∗ denotes [adjoint] of matrix A, σi denotes [singular value] of matrix A, and tr denotes [trace] of matrix.
